Debt-for-Nature Swap Program

â

To convert limited amounts of Philippine foreign debt in to grants for nature, environment and wildlife conservation projects in the Philippines lo be undertaken by international conservation groups;

International Institute of Debt and Development

â

To support the establishment of an International Institute of Debt and Development or any international finance organization that will acquire the debt instruments of the Philippines and other Third World countries at substantial discount, which benefits shall be shared by the debtor countries;

Selective Debt Repudiation

â

To consider the option of selective debt repudiation on foreign loans attended by fraud, bribery, and corruption between foreign lenders and Philippine borrowers;

